HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 334
BY REPRESENTATIVE RISER
A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Susan Ann
Traylor Bittick and to celebrate a remarkable woman whose brilliance, spirit, and
unforgettable presence left a lasting mark on all who knew her.
WHEREAS, Susan was born on September 4, 1954, in Hughes Springs, Texas, to
Robert "Bob" H. Traylor and Jodie Bess Wallace Traylor and was the cherished sister of
Gary Traylor; and
WHEREAS, from her earliest years, Susan was known for her vibrant spirit, warmth,
and ability to bring joy to those around her, qualities that remained hallmarks of her life; and
WHEREAS, Susan graduated from Gilmer High School in 1973 and undertook a
successful journalism career that spanned sixteen years, during which she served as food
editor for the Longview Morning Journal and city editor of the Shreveport Times; and
WHEREAS, Susan's sharp intellect and commanding presence earned her the
opportunity to cover the gubernatorial campaign of former Florida Governor Bob Martinez,
and she later served as his press secretary; and
WHEREAS, Susan relished the opportunity to challenge herself and returned to
school to pursue higher education; she earned a bachelor's degree in Latin American Studies
from Louisiana Tech University in 1990 and went on to attend St. Louis University School
of Law, where she distinguished herself as editor of the Law Journal and graduated in 1995;
and
WHEREAS, in 2006, Susan earned a master of laws degree from the University of
Houston, which further cemented her reputation as a formidable legal and policy mind; and
WHEREAS, Susan devoted the last nineteen years of her accomplished career to
Ryan, LLC, where she most recently served as a principal in the company's U.S. advocacy
practice and earned national recognition as a leading and influential voice in state tax policy;
and
