WHEREAS, Susan was admired by her colleagues and peers for her intellect,
professionalism, integrity, mentorship, extraordinary work ethic, and unwavering
commitment to public service; she is remembered as a dynamic, insightful, and powerful
advocate and described as "wicked smart," "a firecracker," and "a force to be reckoned
with"; and
WHEREAS, Susan was a cherished member of the Louisiana Capitol team,
affectionately known as "The Roses and The Thorns", where her wit, intuition, friendship,
unmistakable personality, and infectious laugh made her deeply admired and treasured
among the group and by all those around her; and
WHEREAS, despite her many professional accomplishments, Susan's greatest joy
was the life she built with her beloved husband, Tom Bittick, whom she met at a Christmas
party in 1990 and married on October 5, 1991; and
WHEREAS, Susan and Tom shared a passion for travel, exceptional food, fine wine,
and new adventures, and she was especially fond of her travels to London and countless
other cities around the world; and
WHEREAS, Susan embraced life with unmistakable style and enthusiasm, never
missed an opportunity to dance, and was rarely seen without her signature heels; and
WHEREAS, Susan was an avid reader, an accomplished gardener known for
producing an abundance of tomatoes and countless jars of homemade marinara sauce, an
avid art collector with exceptional taste and appreciation for fine art, and a devoted lover of
Christmas music on vinyl; she also cherished her beloved dogs, especially her rescue dog,
Mavis; and
WHEREAS, Susan's family game nights were legendary occasions; she often insisted
upon playing Monopoly as the Scottie Dog token and threatened to read the entire rulebook
aloud whenever she suspected cheating; and
WHEREAS, Susan possessed a rare combination of fierce determination, quick wit,
immense kindness, and boundless generosity, and these qualities endeared her to family,
friends, colleagues, and all fortunate enough to cross her path; and
WHEREAS, Susan embraced Louisiana's unique culture and traditions, especially
enjoying annual gatherings and outdoor excursions with dear friends and colleagues that
celebrated the state's rich cuisine, camaraderie, and sporting heritage, particularly her
