memorable alligator hunting adventures and her plans to transform treasured keepsakes from
those experiences into handcrafted items reflecting her adventurous spirit, creativity, and
deep love for Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, Susan leaves behind a legacy of love, wisdom, and devotion to her
family, friends, and colleagues; she is survived by her loving husband of thirty-four years,
Tom Bittick; her brother, Gary Traylor (Chasha); her sisters-in-law, Elizabeth Bittick Dailey
and Mary Bittick Camden (Mike); her uncle, Jerry Traylor; and a host of loving nieces,
nephews, great-nieces, and great-nephews who affectionately knew her as "The Greatest
Aunt"; and
WHEREAS, Susan Ann Traylor Bittick lived boldly, loved deeply, and left behind
a legacy of brilliance, kindness, humor, grace, and unmistakable flair that will continue to
inspire and uplift all who knew and loved her.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Susan
Ann Traylor Bittick and does hereby extend sincere wishes that her family, friends,
colleagues, and loved ones find comfort in their shared memories of her beautiful life.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to her
husband, Tom Bittick, and her brother, Gary Traylor.
